replies.body:
I feel for you man. A similar thing happened to me in Season 1 when they nerfed Evelynn to the ground by removing her stun and lowering her base stats. By then, I had over 500 games on her and she was the only champion I played. It was a hard blow to me but I eventually moved onto other champions when I realised Riot didn't care about the few Evelynn mains there were. A lot of my mains over the years have become FotM and have been nerfed. I learned to adapt.

Well actually, I only adapted because I wanted to be a pro player. Winning became more important than having fun to an extent. If you're really not having fun, I'm sorry for your loss.

